We have studied the patientsβ€™ demographics, clinical presentation, aneurysm size and configuration, type of coils used for embolization, the percentage of compaction and recanalization (especially in patients who presented with subarachnoid hemorrhage), the immediate complications due to the procedure used. We also want to implement the ISAT results in Romanian guidelines, and finally the aneurysms embolization to become the first choice in aneurysms treatment.
