<sections.5>
Conclusions
he treatment of cerebral aneurysms with coils is a safe and durable option with a mortality rate of 2,6% and a risk of recanalization in our cohort of 4,3%.
he interventional neuroradiology can complete the aneurysm treatment in the cases in which the neurosurgery was not enough.
he intraprocedural complications are often not correlated with clinical complications.
ultiple aneurysms patients can be cured in one session.
arger series of patients treated with this method are needed to support our evidence.Conclusions
The treatment of cerebral aneurysms with coils is a safe and durable option with a mortality rate of 2,6% and a risk of recanalization in our cohort of 4,3%.
The interventional neuroradiology can complete the aneurysm treatment in the cases in which the neurosurgery was not enough.
The intraprocedural complications are often not correlated with clinical complications.
Multiple aneurysms patients can be cured in one session.
Larger series of patients treated with this method are needed to support our evidence.
